1086	\leanok
1087	[Chart-ring iso: $\mathrm{Away}\,\mathcal A\,X_i \cong \bar k[u]$]
1088	  \label{def:proj_chart_ring_iso}
1089	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.homogeneousLocalizationAwayIso}
1090	  \uses{def:projlinebar_affine_cover}
1091	  % Archon-original Lean encoding of the textbook identification ``the affine chart of
1092	  % $\mathbb P^1$ at $X_i$ is $\mathbb A^1$ with coordinate $X_{1-i}/X_i$'', expressed at
1093	  % the homogeneous-localization level. No external % SOURCE QUOTE needed.
1094	  For each $i \in \{0, 1\}$, the chart-$i$ ring of $\overline{\mathbb P^1}$ --- the
1095	  degree-zero part $\mathrm{Away}\,\mathcal A\,X_i$ of the localization of the standard
1096	  $\mathbb N$-graded polynomial ring $\bar k[X_0, X_1]$ at $X_i$ --- is isomorphic as a
1097	  $\bar k$-algebra to the one-variable polynomial ring $\bar k[u]$, where the affine
1098	  chart coordinate is $u = X_{1-i}/X_i$. This is the formalisation-level realisation of
1099	  the standard ``affine chart of $\mathbb P^1$ is $\mathbb A^1$'' identification expressed
